cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper focuses on analyzing the biases of deep neural networks, particularly CNNs, in computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also utilizes methods from psychophysics and neurophysiology, indicating a potential fit for cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the performance of different types of neural networks, suggesting a possible fit for cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
